r of the White Eagle (Russia)|Knight of the White Eagle]]\n** Knight 1st Class, [[Order of Saint Anna]]\n** Knight 1st Class, [[Order of Saint Stanislaus (House of Romanov)|Order of St. Stanislaus]]\n* {{flag|Kingdom of Saxony}}: [[Order of the Rue Crown|Knight of the Rue Crown]], 1852<ref>''Staatshandbuch f\u00fcr den Freistaat Sachsen (1867)'' (in German), \"K\u00f6nigliche Ritter-Orden\", p. 4</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Sweden|1844}} {{flagicon|Norway|1844}} [[Sweden-Norway]]: [[Order of the Seraphim|Knight with Collar of the Seraphim]], 21 April 1865\n* {{flagicon|Tuscany|habsburg}} [[Grand Duchy of Tuscany]]: Grand Cross, [[Order of Saint Joseph]]\n* {{flag|Two Sicilies}}\n** Grand Cross, [[Order of Saint Ferdinand and of Merit]].\n** [[Order of Saint Januarius|Knight of St. Januarius]].\n}}\n\n===Coat of arms===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; margin:auto;\"\n| [[File:Coat of Arms of the Second Mexican Empire.svg|250px]]\n|-\n| Coat of Arms of His Imperial Majesty, Maximilian of Mexico\n|}\n\n==Ancestry==\n{{ahnentafel\n|collapsed=yes |align=center\n| boxstyle_1 = background-color: #fcc;\n| boxstyle_2 = background-color: #fb9;\n| boxstyle_3 = background-color: #ffc;\n| boxstyle_4 = background-color: #bfc;\n| boxstyle_5 = background-color: #9fe;\n| 1 = 1. '''Maximilian I of Mexico'''\n| 2 = 2. [[Archduke Franz Karl of Austria]]\n| 3 = 3. [[Princess Sophie of Bavaria]]\n| 4 = 4. [[Francis II, Holy Roman Emperor]]<ref name=\"BLKO-Franz Karl\">{{BLKO|wstitle=Habsburg, Franz Karl Joseph|volume=6|page=257}}</ref>\n| 5 = 5. [[Maria Theresa of Naples and Sicily|Princess Maria Theresa of Naples and Sicily]]<ref name=\"BLKO-Franz Karl\"/>\n| 6 = 6. [[Maximilian I Joseph of Bavaria]]<ref name=\"BLKO-Sophie\">{{BLKO|wstitle=Habsburg, Sophie (geb. 27. J\u00e4nner 1805)|volume=7|page=149}}</ref>\n| 7 = 7. [[Caroline of Baden|Princess Caroline of Baden]]<ref name=\"BLKO-Sophie\"/>\n| 8 = 8. [[Leopold II, Holy Roman Emperor]]<ref name=\"BLKO-Franz I\">{{BLKO|wstitle=Habsburg, Franz I.|volume=6|page=208}}</ref>\n| 9 = 9. [[Maria Luisa of Spain|Infanta Maria Louisa of Spain]]<ref name=\"BLKO-Franz I\"/>\n| 10 = 10. [[Ferdinand I of the Two Sicilies]]<ref name=\"BLKO-Maria Theresia von Neapel\">{{BLKO|wstitle=Habsburg, Maria Theresia von Neapel|volume=7|page=81}}</ref>\n| 11 = 11. [[Maria Carolina of Austria|Archduchess Maria Carolina of Austria]]<ref name=\"BLKO-Maria Theresia von Neapel\"/>\n| 12 = 12. [[Frederick Michael, Count Palatine of Zweibr\u00fccken]]<ref name=\"Genealogie94\">{{cite book|title=Genealogie ascendante jusqu'au quatrieme degre inclusivement de tous les Rois et Princes de maisons souveraines de l'Europe actuellement vivans| trans-title=Genealogy up to the fourth degree inclusive of all the Kings and Princes of sovereign houses of Europe currently living |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=AINPAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA94|year=1768|publisher=Frederic Guillaume Birnstiel|location=Bourdeaux|language=fr|page=94}}</ref>\n| 13 = 13. [[Countess Palatine Maria Franziska of Sulzbach]]<ref name=\"Genealogie94\"/>\n| 14 = 14. [[Charles Louis, Hereditary Prince of Baden]]<ref name=\"HDBG\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.hdbg.eu/biografien/web/index.php/detail?uid=1351 |title=Karoline Friederike Wilhelmine K\u00f6nigin von Bayern |website=Haus der Bayerischen Geschichte [House of Bavarian History] |publisher=Bavarian Ministry of State for Wissenschaft and Kunst |language=de |access-date=2018-11-30 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n| 15 = 15. [[Princess Amalie of Hesse-Darmstadt]]<ref name=\"HDBG\"/>\n}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of heads of state of Mexico]] \n* [[Column of Pedro IV]]\n* [[List of people from Morelos, Mexico]]\n* [[Acapantzingo, Cuernavaca]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{refbegin|colwidth=30em}}\n{{Ordered list|type=upper-alpha|\n{{note label|specialnotes1|A|none}} \"Such an easy assumption of an improbable sexual relationship\", said Alan Palmer, \"fails to understand the nature of the attachment binding\" Sophie and Reichstadt, who saw themselves as alien misfits stranded in a foreign court.{{sfn|Palmer|1994|p=3}} To Palmer, their \"confidences were those of a brother and elder sister rather than of lovers\".{{sfn|Palmer|1994|p=3}} \"There is no documentary evidence to suggest that she and the Duke of Reichstadt were ever lovers\", according to Joan Haslip.{{sfn|Haslip|1972|p=4}} \"Whether the young Napoleon was actually the father of Maximilian could only be the subject of fascinating conjecture, something for courtiers and servants to gossip about on the long winter nights in the [[Hofburg Palace|Hofburg]] [Palace]\", said Richard O'Connor.{{sfn|O'Connor|1971|p=31}} \"There is not a shred of evidence to support the rumors\", affirmed Jasper Ridley.{{sfn|Ridley|2001|p=44}} \"It was said that Sophie confessed\", continued Ridley, \"in a letter to her father confessor, that Maximilian was the son of Napoleon, and that the letter was found and destroyed in 1859, but there is no reason to believe this story ... would she have had a sexual relationship with a boy whom she regarded as a child and a younger brother?\"{{sfn|Ridley|2001|p=45}} The birth of two more sons after the death of Reichstadt in 1832 lessened even more the credibility of these claims.{{sfn|Ridley|2001|p=45}}\n}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==Citations==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=17em}}\n\n==References==\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book |last=Harding |first=Bertita|title=Phantom Crown: The story of Maximilian & Carlota of Mexico |year=1934 |publisher=Blue Ribbon Books |location=New York |isbn=1434468925 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Haslip |first=Joan |title=The Crown of Mexico: Maximilian and His Empress Carlota |year=1972 |publisher=Holt, Rinehart and Winston |location=New York |isbn=0-03-086572-7 |ref=harv |url=https://archive.org/details/crownofmexicomax00hasl }}\n* {{cite book |last=Hyde |first=H. Montgomery |title=Mexican Empire: the history of Maximilian and Carlota of Mexico |year=1946 |publisher=Macmillan & Co. |location=London |isbn= |ref=harv