| Kendall Trudgen ([[Independent (politician)|Ind]])\n|-\n|[[Electoral division of Nightcliff|Nightcliff]] || [[Australian Labor Party (Northern Territory Branch)|Labor]] || {{Australian party shading/Labor}}|[[Natasha Fyles]] || Kim Loveday || Owen Gale || Andrew Arthur ([[Independent (politician)|Ind]])<br />Stuart Blanch ([[Independent (politician)|Ind]])<br />Peter Rudge ([[Independent (politician)|Ind]])<br />Felicity Wardle ([[Australian Sex Party|ASP]])\n|-\n|[[Electoral division of Port Darwin|Port Darwin]] || [[Country Liberal Party|CLP]] || Alan James || {{Australian party shading/CLP}}|'''[[John Elferink]]''' || David Andrews || Rowena Leunig ([[Australian Sex Party|ASP]])\n|-\n|[[Electoral division of Sanderson|Sanderson]] || [[Country Liberal Party|CLP]] || Jodie Green || {{Australian party shading/CLP}}|'''[[Peter Styles (politician)|Peter Styles]]''' || || Jillian Briggs ([[Australian Sex Party|ASP]])<br />Dimitrious Magriplis ([[Australia's First Nations Political Party|FNPP]])\n|-\n|[[Electoral division of Stuart|Stuart]] || [[Australian Labor Party (Northern Territory Branch)|Labor]] || '''[[Karl Hampton]]''' || {{Australian party shading/CLP}}|[[Bess Price]] || || Maurie Japarta Ryan ([[Australia's First Nations Political Party|FNPP]])\n|-\n|[[Electoral division of Wanguri|Wanguri]] || [[Australian Labor Party (Northern Territory Branch)|Labor]] || {{Australian party shading/Labor}}|'''[[Paul Henderson (politician)|Paul Henderson]]''' || Rhianna Harker || || \n|}\n\n=== Unregistered parties and groups ===\n* Two previous [[One Nation (Australia)|One Nation]] candidates ran, One Nation Northern Territory Branch President John Kearney in [[Electoral division of Goyder|Goyder]] and Peter Bussa from NSW in [[Electoral division of Johnston|Johnston]].\n\n== Pre-election pendulum ==\nThe following pendulum is known as the [[Mackerras Pendulum]], invented by [[psephology|psephologist]] [[Malcolm Mackerras]]. The pendulum works by lining up all of the seats held in the [[Northern Territory Legislative Assembly|Legislative Assembly]] according to the [[percentage point]] margin they are held by on a two-party-preferred basis. This is also known as the [[Swing (Australian politics)|swing]] required for the seat to change hands. Given a uniform swing to the opposition or government parties, the number of seats that change hands can be predicted.\n\n{| class=\"toccolours\" align=\"left\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-right: .5em; margin-top: .4em;font-size: 90%;\" float:left\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"  style=\"text-align:center; background:red;\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">'''LABOR SEATS'''</span>\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"  style=\"text-align:center; background:red;\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">'''Marginal'''</span>\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ffcaca;\"|[[Electoral division of Fannie Bay|Fannie Bay]]\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ffcaca;\"|[[Michael Gunner]]\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ffcaca;\"|ALP\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ffcaca;\"|1.1\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ffcaca;\"|[[Electoral division of Daly|Daly]]\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ffcaca;\"|[[Rob Knight (politician)|Robert Knight]]\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ffcaca;\"|ALP\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ffcaca;\"|5.6\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"  style=\"text-align:center; background:red;\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">'''Fairly safe'''</span>\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff8d8d;\"|[[Electoral division of Johnston|Johnston]]\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff8d8d;\"|[[Chris Burns (politician)|Chris Burns]]\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff8d8d;\"|ALP\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff8d8d;\"|8.1\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"  style=\"text-align:center; background:red;\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">'''Safe'''</span>\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|[[Electoral division of Nightcliff|Nightcliff]]\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|[[Jane Aagaard]]\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|ALP\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|10.7\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|[[Electoral division of Karama|Karama]]\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|[[Delia Lawrie]]\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|ALP\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|10.8\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|[[Electoral division of Arafura|Arafura]]\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|[[Marion Scrymgour]]\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|ALP\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|14.0\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|[[Electoral division of Casuarina|Casuarina]]\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|[[Kon Vatskalis]]\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|ALP\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|14.2\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|[[Electoral division of Wanguri|Wanguri]]\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|[[Paul Henderson (politician)|Paul Henderson]]\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|ALP\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|14.9\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|[[Electoral division of Stuart|Stuart]]\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|[[Karl Hampton]]\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|ALP\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|15.1\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|[[Electoral division of Barkly|Barkly]]\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|[[Gerry McCarthy]]\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|ALP\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ff6b6b;\"|15.6\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"  style=\"text-align:center; background:red;\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">'''Very safe'''</span>\n|-\n| 