l the World's Aircraft 2000\u201301 |editor1-last=Jackson |editor1-first=Paul|year=2000 |publisher=Jane's Information Group |location=Coulsdon, Surrey, United Kingdom |isbn=978-0710620118 |edition=91st |pages=22-24}}</ref>{{importance-inline|reason=not sure it deserve its own column as it is the ERJ145LR/XR with lower weights}}\n|-\n! Crew\n| colspan=4 | 3 (2 pilots + flight attendant)\n|-\n! Seating\n| 37\n| 44\n| colspan=2 | 50\n|-\n! Length\n| 26.33 m (86&nbsp;ft 5 in)\n| 28.45 m (93&nbsp;ft 4 in)\n| colspan=2 | 29.87 m (98&nbsp;ft 0 in)\n|-\n! Wing span\n| colspan=4 | 20.04 m (65&nbsp;ft 9 in)\n|-\n! Wing\n| colspan=4 | {{cvt|51.18|m2}} area, [[wing aspect ratio|aspect ratio]] 7.9, supercritical airfoil<ref name=\"Selig\">{{cite web |last1=Lednicer |first1=David |title=The Incomplete Guide to Airfoil Usage |url=https://m-selig.ae.illinois.edu/ads/aircraft.html |website=m-selig.ae.illinois.edu |accessdate=16 April 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! Height\n| colspan=4 |6.76 m (22&nbsp;ft 2 in)\n|-\n! [[Maximum Take Off Weight|MTOW]]\n| ER: 19,000&nbsp;kg (41,887&nbsp;lb)<br />LR: 20,000&nbsp;kg (44,092&nbsp;lb)\n| ER: 20,100&nbsp;kg (44,312&nbsp;lb)<br />LR: 21,100&nbsp;kg (46,517&nbsp;lb)\n| LR: 22,000&nbsp;kg (48,501&nbsp;lb)<br />XR: 24,100&nbsp;kg (53,131&nbsp;lb)\n| {{cvt|20600|kg|0}} \n|-\n! [[Operating empty weight|BOW]]\n| ER: 11,402&nbsp;kg / 25,137&nbsp;lb <br />LR: 11,501&nbsp;kg / 25,355&nbsp;lb\n| ER: 11,816&nbsp;kg / 26,049&nbsp;lb <br />LR:  11,808&nbsp;kg / 26,032&nbsp;lb\n| LR: 12,114&nbsp;kg / 26,706&nbsp;lb<br />XR: 12,591&nbsp;kg / 27,758&nbsp;lb\n| {{cvt|11700|kg|0}}\n|-\n! Max payload\n| ER: 4,198&nbsp;kg (9,255&nbsp;lb)<br />LR: 4,499&nbsp;kg (9,918&nbsp;lb)\n| ER: 5,284&nbsp;kg (11,649&nbsp;lb)<br />LR: 5,292&nbsp;kg (11,666&nbsp;lb)\n| LR: 5,786&nbsp;kg (12,755&nbsp;lb)<br />XR: 5,909&nbsp;kg (13,027&nbsp;lb)\n| {{cvt|5400|kg|0}}\n|-\n! Fuel capacity\n| colspan=3 | ER: 5,146l / 1,359gal, LR: 6,396l / 1,690gal, XR: 7,438l / 1,965gal\n| {{cvt|4173|kg|0}}\